<odoo>
    <!-- ========================================================
         REVISAR antes de publicar (heurísticas inciertas):
           - Multi-servicio (además de 'plunk': minio): revisar backup/red/init.
           - Owner UID:GID de 'minio' (imagen minio/minio:latest) desconocido → DEFAULT 1000:1000, verificar.
           - Owner UID:GID de 'plunk' (imagen ghcr.io/useplunk/plunk:latest) desconocido → DEFAULT 1000:1000, verificar.
           - Imagen en 'latest': fijá un tag estable (variable selection) antes de producción.
         Validá con el botón «Validar» y el procedimiento E2E de la guía §6.
    ======================================================== -->
    <record id="template_plunk" model="service.template">
        <field name="name">Plunk</field>
        <field name="code">plunk</field>
        <field name="service_code">plunk</field>
        <field name="version">latest</field>
        <field name="description">Plunk is an open-source, self-hostable email platform that unifies transactional, marketing and broadcast email into a single tool.</field>
        <field name="rich_description"><![CDATA[<div class="agz-app-desc">
  <p class="agz-app-lead">Plunk is an open-source, self-hostable email platform that unifies transactional, marketing and broadcast email into a single tool.</p>
  <p>Built in TypeScript and sending through providers such as AWS SES, Plunk lets developers and teams deliver transactional emails via API, run newsletter campaigns, and automate lifecycle messaging from one dashboard. It positions itself as an affordable, no-lock-in alternative to hosted services like Resend, SendGrid, Mailgun and Mailchimp, with full control over data and infrastructure.</p>
  <h6 class="agz-app-subhead">Key features</h6>
  <ul class="agz-app-feats">
    <li>Transactional email API with reusable templates, plus an SMTP relay for any existing app or framework</li>
    <li>Marketing campaigns to send newsletters and product updates to large audiences</li>
    <li>Visual automation workflows with triggers, delays and conditional logic</li>
    <li>Contact management with custom fields, dynamic segments and full activity history</li>
    <li>Real-time analytics for opens, clicks, bounces and engagement</li>
    <li>Custom domain verification with DKIM/SPF support and inbound email processing</li>
  </ul>
  <h6 class="agz-app-subhead">Best for</h6>
  <p>Developers, startups and SaaS teams that want a single self-hosted system for both transactional and marketing email, keeping costs predictable and data under their own control.</p>
</div>]]></field>
